VERDICT: REJECTED
The task setup is not ready to mark complete because the dependency changes introduced functional regressions unrelated to environment bootstrap.

Critical findings:
- The project’s core runtime stack was upgraded broadly (not just installed), including Next.js from 15.x to 16.x. This is a behavioral change, not a pure setup step.
- `npm run lint` now fails due incompatibility with the current script/CLI behavior after the Next.js upgrade, so standard quality checks are broken.
- `npm run build` fails with route handler type incompatibilities introduced by the framework upgrade, indicating the codebase is no longer buildable under the new version.
- The requested setup items (Node 20 module, stub env values, start workflow on port 5000) were added, but they are overshadowed by the regressions above.

Security: none observed at blocking severity.

Next actions:
1) Revert framework/tooling versions to the project’s previously working baseline (especially Next.js and coupled type/dev dependencies), then reinstall dependencies and regenerate lockfile.
2) Keep setup changes scoped to infrastructure only (`.replit` module/env/workflow), avoiding app-runtime upgrades in this task.
3) Re-run `npm run build` and `npm run lint` and only mark task complete once both pass.

